On Wed, Jul 12, 2000 at 11:55:42AM -0400, Mark Hahn wrote:
> > same mount point without getting errors. I think this is a bug as it prevents
> > clean unmounting if you reboot. If a partition get mounted twice and you reboot,
> no, it's a feature.  you merely have to unmount N times.
Ok, I agree more or less (also I don't understand the benefit), as 'umount -a'
works.
BUT why doesn't a partition mounted twice an unmounted once show up in 'mount'?
I don't really think you can declare this a feature.
